  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Legal definitions typically involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source through multiple transactions\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the funds into the legitimate economy\n\nSpecific legal elements usually include:\n- Knowingly concealing the origins of criminal proceeds\n- Attempting to disguise the true nature of illegally obtained funds\n- Transforming cash or assets derived from criminal activity\n- Transferring money to hide its illegal source\n\nExact definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but most follow similar core principles established by international anti-money laundering frameworks.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering definitions?",
